// A module-PRIVATE generic record (`Slot<T>`) used only as the element of a
// pub `Store<T>`'s `Vec<Slot<T>>`, monomorphised across a module boundary to a
// `string` payload (#2755).
//
// `Slot<T>` is never nameable by the importer and never emitted as a HIR item,
// so before #2755 the consumer had no `RecordLayout` for it: the `Slot { .. }`
// construction inside `Store::add` dropped its type args and `Vec::push` on the
// type-parameter element failed closed. The layout is now discovered from the
// substituted `Store::add$$string` body's type structure, keyed bare, and the
// heap-owning `string` payload round-trips through the private slot.
//
// Reading `generation_at` back proves the private record's field-order table
// resolved end-to-end cross-module.
//
// Harness verb: hew run
// Expected: two generation stamps, one per inserted value (0 then 1).
import hew::privslot;

fn main() {
    let store: privslot.Store<string> = privslot.new();
    store.add("hello");
    store.add("world");
    println(store.generation_at(0));
    println(store.generation_at(1));
}
